set the http headers to be sent from the client to the server.

public void sendPostRequest(String[] parameters)
do a http POST request with the post data sent with header "content-type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded". Set the header to "content-type: multipart/form-data" to send as multipart.

Parameters:

If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.

createDateString

public void createDateString(String[] parameters)
Create a datestring with the current time and specified formating. The used Locale will be US. Default timezone is system timezone. Default no seconds will be added to the time value.

Parameters:
parameters - array of String containing the parameters. parameters[0] argument is always the method name, parameters[1] is a time format allowed by java.text.SimpleDateFormat. parameters[2] is the variable name to store the created datestring in. parameters[3] (optional) numer of seconds to add to the time value. (3600, -3600 etc.) parameters[4] (optional, requeires parameter[3]) Timezone to use in java.util.TimeZone.getTimeZone(parameter[4]) format. If null is used as parameters it sends the allowed parameters list to the XTTProperties.printFail(java.lang.String) method and returns.
